comment_data.body:
_From @scheglov on February 19, 2016 0:28_

Yes, DAS has [the extension point](https://github.com/dart-lang/sdk/blob/master/pkg/analysis_server/lib/plugin/edit/fix/fix.dart) for fixes.

_From @sethladd on February 19, 2016 0:29_

Nice! Looking forward to using them :)

_From @sethladd on November 14, 2016 23:8_

Should we move this, and other "affects: jetbrains-plugin" to their issue tracker?

cc @mit-mit

_From @pq on November 14, 2016 23:26_

> Should we move this, and other "affects: jetbrains-plugin" to their issue tracker?

SGTM. 

Incidentally, IDEA has it's own mechanism for code boiler-plate.  An alternative to using a DAS plugin, would be to contribute some [live code templates](https://blog.jetbrains.com/webide/2012/10/high-speed-coding-with-custom-live-templates/) to the Flutter plugin.  Not as smart since they can't leverage all that the analyzer but maybe in this case that's OK?

_From @sethladd on November 14, 2016 23:31_

Yeah, I think we need something like "smart" live code templates. We need to know if we're wrapping with something that takes a single child or multiple children.

_From @sethladd on November 15, 2016 16:25_

> https://github.com/flutter/flutter-intellij/issues

Sorry, that's what I meant.

I strongly believe that this functionality should live in DAS and its plugins.

I can imagine a lint for Flutter, which for example will complain when you have `children` with a single widget, when you could use `child`. A Quick Fix for this lint is a bit more complex than AFAIK IntelliJ code templates allow, so you would implement it in DAS.

But then why to have some code transformations in IntelliJ, and some in DAS? And of course these Quick Assists are very resolution specific - it would be sad to pollute assist menu with actions that don't make sense in the context.
Hi @scheglov I am not familiar with the experience you get from DAS assists, can you give an example of a current one and how to 'trigger it'?
@scheglov, we can consider this a tracking issue for the functionality, and the implementation can live elsewhere. This would be a good use-case for a flutter specific analysis server plugin.

@mit-mit

Your keyboard shortcut may be different.

> I strongly believe that this functionality should live in DAS and its plugins.

Yes, please!
I heard this feature was shown in a recent demo.
